0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 4 "The " }{TEXT 259 16 "Binomial Theor
em" }{TEXT -1 66 " gives a formula for finding the coefficients of the
 expansion of " }{XPPEDIT 18 0 "(a+b)^n;" "6#),&%\"aG\"\"\"%\"bGF&%\"n
G" }{TEXT -1 10 "  for any " }{TEXT 267 1 "n" }{TEXT -1 53 ".  It is r
elatively obvious that the coefficient of  " }{XPPEDIT 18 0 "a^(n-k)*b
^k;" "6#*&)%\"aG,&%\"nG\"\"\"%\"kG!\"\"F()%\"bGF)F(" }{TEXT -1 19 "  f
or any value of " }{TEXT 268 1 "k" }{TEXT -1 11 " from 0 to " }{TEXT 
269 1 "n" }{TEXT -1 46 " is given by the number of ways we can choose \+
" }{TEXT 270 1 "k" }{TEXT -1 8 " of the " }{TEXT 294 1 "b" }{TEXT -1 
12 "'s from the " }{TEXT 271 1 "n" }{TEXT -1 1 " " }{TEXT 295 1 "b" }
{TEXT -1 20 "'s in the expansion " }{XPPEDIT 18 0 "(a+b)*(a+b)" "6#*&,
&%\"aG\"\"\"%\"bGF&F&,&F%F&F'F&F&" }{TEXT -1 7 " ....( " }{XPPEDIT 18 
0 "(a+b)" "6#,&%\"aG\"\"\"%\"bGF%" }{TEXT -1 5 " ),  " }{TEXT 272 1 "n
" }{TEXT -1 41 " times .   The number of combinations of " }{TEXT 273 
1 "n" }{TEXT -1 18 " objects choosing " }{TEXT 274 1 "k" }{TEXT -1 12 
" at a time, " }{XPPEDIT 18 0 "nCk" "6#%$nCkG" }{TEXT -1 27 ", is give
n by the formula  " }{XPPEDIT 18 0 "nCk=n!/(k!*(n-k)!)" "6#/%$nCkG*&-%
*factorialG6#%\"nG\"\"\"*&-F'6#%\"kGF*-F'6#,&F)F*F.!\"\"F*F2" }{TEXT 
-1 2 " ." }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT 261 
10 "State the " }{TEXT 260 16 "Binomial Theorem" }{TEXT -1 1 " " }
{TEXT 275 31 "and use Maple to demonstrate it" }{TEXT -1 1 "." }}
{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 71 "The Binomial Theorem expands (a+b)^n and \+
gives the coefficients for it." }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}
