tions.  In this exericse we study the basic properties of polynomials \+
and rational functions.  Some revelant MAPLE commands will be   factor
, expand, solve, fsolve, denom, numer, simplify, subs,   ....... ." }}
{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 171 "     The first thing we need to learn is
 how to define a function.  There are two ways, each with its own adva
ntages and disadvantages.  First define the polynomial p1 as " }{TEXT 
282 2 "a " }{TEXT -1 1 "s" }{TEXT 283 23 "ymbolic expression in x" }
{TEXT -1 119 " in the following way:    p1:=x^2-1;  (Note the colon be
fore the =, this is always required when defining something.)  " }}
{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 10 "p1:=x^2-1;" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 
"" {XPPMATH 20 "6#>%#p1G,&*$)%\"xG\"\"#\"\"\"F*F*!\"\"" }}}{PARA 0 "" 
0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 39 "     Now define the \+
same polynomial as " }{TEXT 281 30 "an operation on the variable x" }
{TEXT -1 40 " in the following way:     p2:=x->x^2-1;" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 
"" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 13 "p2:=x->x^
2-1;" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#>%#p2Gf*6#%\"xG6\"6$%)operator
